   "source": [
    "# Linear Relation Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "> This function considers linear relationships between two pollutants. The relationships\n",
    "are calculated on different times bases using a linear model. The slope and 95 %\n",
    "confidence interval in slope relationships by time unit are plotted in several different\n",
    "ways. The function is particularly useful when considering whether relationships are\n",
    "consistent with emissions inventories.\n",
    "The relationships between pollutants can yield some very useful information about\n",
    "source emissions and how they change. A scatter plot between two pollutants is\n",
    "the usual way to investigate the relationship. A linear regression is useful to test the\n",
    "strength of the relationship. However, considerably more information can be gleaned\n",
    "by considering different time periods, such as how the relationship between two\n",
    "pollutants vary over time, by day of the week, diurnally and so on. The linearRelation\n",
    "function does just that â€” it fits a linear relationship between two pollutants over a wide\n",
    "range of time periods determined by period."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Standard libraries to be imported for usage"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "from vayu import linearRelation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "linearRelation(df, 'nox', 'so2')"
